 2. Evaluate sensor noise characteristics under various conditions

- Understand how stable the readings are and what affects noise.

via:
Test the sensor under different conditions:

    Static pressure (holding steady) – measure standard deviation

    Dynamic pressure (tapping, squeezing) – measure response consistency

    Temperature – does heat affect readings? (use a heat gun or cold spray)

    Humidity – does moisture affect readings? (try with damp fingers)

    Time drift – does the reading change over 1 hour of constant pressure?

    Vibration – does shaking the wire cause noise?

