 3-   Investigate the effect of bending sensor leads and sensing areas

 Know if bending the wires or sensor body changes readings.

via:
Test the sensor in different physical configurations:

    Wire bending: Bend the leads at various angles (0°, 45°, 90°, 180°)

    Sensor bending: Curve the sensor itself (concave/convex)

    Lead length: Test with different wire lengths (10cm, 30cm, 1m)

    Twisting: Twist the wires and observe if readings change



Configuration          | ADC at light touch | ADC at hard press | Notes
-----------------------|-------------------|-------------------|--------
Leads straight         | 200               | 3500              | Baseline
Leads bent 90°         | 198               | 3495              | No significant change
Leads bent 180°        | 195               | 3480              | Slight drop
Sensor curved          | 220               | 3400              | Less sensitivity
Sensor bent sharply    | 250               | 3200              | Significant change



