5. Evaluate conductive yarn and flexible trace wiring options

 Test alternative wiring methods that are flexible and durable for a wearable glove.

via:
Test different flexible connection options:
Option  Description Pros    Cons
Conductive yarn Sewn-in conductive thread   Flexible, wearable  Higher resistance, fragile
Flexible PCB    Thin flexible circuit board Reliable, consistent    More expensive
Silicone wire   Fine-stranded copper with silicone insulation   Very flexible   Thicker, may break over time
Enameled copper wire    Thin, coated wire   Very thin   Brittle with repeated bending
Stretchable conductive fabric   Fabric with conductive properties   Comfortable Resistance changes with stretch

For each wiring option:

    Resistance measurement: Measure wire resistance per meter

    Bend test: Bend the wire 1000 times, measure resistance change

    Flex test: Simulate finger movement for 1000 cycles

    Noise test: Compare signal noise with each wiring type

    Wash test: Can it survive washing? (if needed)

